    "stress_mark": "ˈ",
    "notes": "Stress per the Académia Ligùstica do Brénno grafia ofiçiâ. The default position is paroxytone (penultimate), as in most Gallo-Italic. Any orthographically accented vowel (grave à è ì ò ù, acute é ó, circumflex â ê î ô û, diaeresis ä ë ï ö ü, and the ligature æ) marks the stressed syllable and always wins; the circumflex and diaeresis additionally encode vowel length. This is an orthographic-encoding simplification: the grafia writes the accent precisely so stress is recoverable from the spelling."
  },
